      "amount": "1 tablespoon",
      "notes": "balance sweetness"
    },
    {
      "name": "Rice",
      "amount": "2 cups",
      "notes": "uncooked"
    },
    {
      "name": "Fresh cilantro",
      "amount": "1/4 cup",
      "notes": "chopped, for garnish"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Heat coconut oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.",
    "Add shrimp and cook until pink, about 2-3 minutes per side. Set aside.",
    "In the same skillet, add curry paste and cook, stirring constantly, for 1-2 minutes.",
    "Add fish sauce, brown sugar, and xtra-hot red pepper flakes. Stir to combine.",
    "Add cooked shrimp back into the skillet and stir to coat with the curry sauce.",
    "Serve over cooked rice and garnish with chopped cilantro."
